thread.title_full: Labor backdown on China trade deal inevitable: govt | Business Spectator

author: AAP
title: Labor backdown on China trade deal inevitable: govt
text:
Labor was always going to vote for Australia's free trade agreement with China despite their campaign against it, government frontbencher Jamie Briggs believes.
The federal opposition will reportedly insist on changes to the Migration Act to mandate market testing before the importation of workers to apply generally to all free trade deals, without amending the China agreement.
"Rather than an olive branch, it's sort of like a Tarzan rope down from a position they couldn't hold," Mr Briggs told ABC radio on Thursday.
